From the manufacturer

Graco SlimFit 3-in-1 Car Seat

The Graco SlimFit 3-in-1 Car Seat grows with your child, from rear-facing harness (5-40 lb) to forward-facing harness (22-65 lb) to highback booster (40-100 lb). It saves space in your back seat, while giving your child plenty of room to grow. The unique, rotating cup holders simply rotate away, making the seat 10% slimmer to save precious back seat space. The seat is Graco ProtectPlus Engineered to help protect your little one in frontal, side, rear, and rollover crashes.

The perfect car seat for:

  • Parents looking for a 3-in-1 car seat to grow with their child, from 5-100 lb
  • Families who want a slimmer car seat that saves space in the back seat

Fantastic Features

Space-Saving Design

A slim design with dual integrated cup holders that rotate away, making the seat 10% slimmer to save valuable back seat space.

ProtectPlus Engineered

This combination of the most rigorous crash tests helps to protect your child in frontal, side, rear & rollover crashes.

No-Rethread Simply Safe Adjust Harness

Adjust the height of your harness and headrest in one motion with the Simply Safe Adjust Harness System, ensuring your child is always properly secured.

10-Position Headrest

Choose the perfect headrest height from 10 positions to get the safest fit for your child as they grow.

More to Love

4-Position Recline

4-position recline allows for a better installation and helps keep your growing child comfy.

InRight LATCH

Push-button InRight LATCH provides an easy, one-second attachment.

Steel-Reinforced Frame

Steel-reinforced frame provides strength and durability for 10 years of use.

Safety Information

To learn about the safe use of car seats and correct installation, visit the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA). Disclaimer: NHTSA doesn't endorse this item. The link is for informational purposes.
See more

Product Description

The Graco SlimFit 3-in-1 Car Seat grows with your child, from rear-facing harness (5-40 lb.) to forward-facing harness (22-65 lb.) to highback booster (40-100 lb). It saves space in your back seat, while giving your child plenty of room to grow. The unique, rotating cup holders simply rotate away, making the seat 10% slimmer to save precious back seat space. The Simply Safe Adjust Harness System means you can easily adjust the harness and headrest together, to accommodate your growing child with ease. With 4 recline positions, you can keep your child comfortable, while the InRight LATCH system makes installation easy with a one-second attachment. The seat is Graco ProtectPlus Engineered to help protect your little one in frontal, side, rear, and rollover crashes.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

LP
4.0 out of 5 stars Good product with caveats
Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2023
Style: SlimFitColor: DarcieVerified Purchase
Just moved closer to grandchildren and needed a car seat for our 2 year old granddaughter. I studied many and this one was comparatively affordable.

Things I liked - it's a little slimmer than other car seats, which is good for our Prius. It seems very sturdy and safe, especially once I was able to figure out how everything connected. I think there is plenty of room for our sturdily sized granddaughter, although we're not expecting long car trips with her at least for a while.

Less happy-making things - the color was not the same as I ordered, the infant insert is brownish, and that's probably an Amazon thing, but it's a minimal issue for me. The directions were actually quite hard to understand, and I have put together/installed lots of things over my many years. Having some arthritis in my fingers did not help with the latch installation, had to call my son over to help with the final one, since I'd already done it one time before but had it slightly wrong. When I looked for online videos to help understand the process, there were some for a newer LX version of this one that were pretty similar but I hate having to search for videos when the company should provide clear directions that give a clear sense of how the car seat latching system works, given that there are several ways for this one seat to be installed. Also, said grandchild's feet were already kicking my seat, something we'll have to talk about.

All in all, I think this is a very good car seat, I just went on about the installation because this grandma's back and hands are just now recovering from that process. The kid should be fine.
